snippet.textDisplay:
A bit of clarity, Sir:
Most cars have resistive touch screens meaning you can still use the screen with gloves on.
Reverse lights are actually intended to provide light behind you when reversing. Programmable reverse lights are to illuminate the rear of your car when parking in a garage etc. Very good idea as most cars only use standard head and tail lights.
The reverse beep in cars is to remind the idiot drivers of the world that their car is in reverse.
And dude, how can you put a picture of a Toyota up when bashing Honda...?
I enjoy your content dude, but please don't let comedic value override factual stuff.

snippet.textDisplay: I think Tesla is in the right direction towards self driving. However not quite there yet.   I think they are putting too much distractions in cars. Touch screens are not good for anything other than infotainment.   I think having dedicated knobs for volume works better/more precise. Having Hvac knobs that you can instantly choose what you need. That allows muscle memory so you don't take your eyes off the road.   Using a full on shifter for the PRNDL allows you to KNOW what your doing.   A good case of this: Jeep ran over owner.
